# Phase 3: Feature-Based Test Organization (HIGH PRIORITY)

**Status:** 🟠 In planning — branch: `phase-3-feature-organization`
**Last Updated:** January 26, 2026
**Context:** Phase 2 (test type reorganization) is complete — this document focuses only on Phase 3: migrating tests to feature/use-case files and implementing naming conventions and discovery improvements.

---

## Problem Statement

- Monolithic test files (e.g., `e2e/api.rs`, `testcontainers_integration.rs`) mix unrelated features and grow too large.
- Poor test naming and ambiguous scopes (e.g., `test_full_lifecycle()`, `api_test_health_endpoints()`).
- Hard to discover tests by feature or reason about ownership.

---

## Goals

- One test file per feature/use-case (module-per-feature organization).
- Consistent naming convention: `feature_scenario_expected()`.
- Test file names clearly indicate the feature (e.g., `object_upload_tests.rs`).
- Keep files focused (<150 lines) and high test density.

---

## Naming Conventions

- Test functions: `feature_scenario_expected()`
  Examples: `object_upload_succeeds_when_valid_payload()`, `health_endpoint_returns_ok()`
- File names: `{scope}_{feature}_tests.rs` or `feature_{scope}_tests.rs`
  Examples: `e2e/api/object_lifecycle_tests.rs`, `integration/use_cases/upload_object_tests.rs`

---

## Target File Layout (migration goal)

integration/use_cases/

- `upload_object_tests.rs`      # Upload use case only
- `download_object_tests.rs`    # Download use case only
- `delete_object_tests.rs`      # Delete use case only
- `search_object_tests.rs`      # Search behavior tests
- `list_objects_tests.rs`       # Listing behavior tests

e2e/api/

- `health_endpoints_tests.rs`   # /health, /health/ready
- `object_lifecycle_tests.rs`   # POST/GET/DELETE /v1/objects
- `api_key_management_tests.rs` # /v1/api-keys
- `search_endpoints_tests.rs`   # /v1/search, /v1/text-search
- `security_tests.rs`           # Auth, CORS, headers, validation

property/

- `value_object_properties.rs`
- `entity_properties.rs`
- `validation_properties.rs`
- `encoding_properties.rs`

---

## Migration Plan (file-by-file)

1. Split `e2e/api.rs` into focused files (health, object lifecycle, api keys, search, security).
2. Split `testcontainers_integration.rs` into integration/use_cases/* (upload/download/delete/search/list).
3. Split `property_tests.rs` into domain property files.
4. Move shared helpers into `tests/common/` (if not already).
5. Delete monolithic source files after verification and ensure git history is preserved.

Notes: Perform changes incrementally — move code, update `use` paths, run `cargo test --workspace` after each move.

---

## Success Criteria

- Each test file <150 lines and focused on a single feature. ✅
- Test names follow `feature_scenario_expected()` convention. ✅
- Easy to find tests for a given endpoint or use case. ✅
- Full test suite passes locally and in CI after each migration step.

---

## Implementation Tasks (Phase 3)

- [ ] Create `e2e/api/health_endpoints_tests.rs` (move health tests)
- [ ] Create `e2e/api/object_lifecycle_tests.rs` (move POST/GET/DELETE tests)
- [ ] Create `e2e/api/api_key_management_tests.rs` (move API key tests)
- [ ] Create `e2e/api/search_endpoints_tests.rs` (move search tests)
- [ ] Create `e2e/api/security_tests.rs` (auth, validation, headers)
- [ ] Split `testcontainers_integration.rs` into `integration/use_cases/*` files
- [ ] Split `property_tests.rs` into domain-specific property files
- [ ] Add per-feature `mod.rs` entries where needed to preserve test discovery
- [ ] Run full test suite and fix any path/visibility issues
- [ ] Delete old monolithic files when coverage is preserved

---

## Quick Commands

- Run test suite: `cargo test --workspace`
- Run a single file: `cargo test --test name_of_test_binary` (after `[[test]]` entries)
- Run a single test: `cargo test <test_name> -- --exact --nocapture`

